&lt;p&gt;When you lean into a sander on a warm afternoon, the first sign of trouble isn’t always visible—it’s the smell. A whisper of scorched wood sugars, a hint of resin in the air, and then a faint glaze that turns your disc into a coaster. That’s what sent me back to our shop’s bench to reassess how we choose abrasives. If you’ve ever wondered why open coat sandpaper runs cooler on gummy woods yet some discs still curl at the edges or shed grit under heat, you’re paying attention to the right variables. The abrasive grain gets much of the spotlight, but the unsung hero—or the weakest link—is the backing and its ability to ride out heat.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/15.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/29/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/heat-resistance-of-different-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>When To Choose Cloth Or Fiber Backings</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 07 Jan 2026 15:23:39 +0000</pubDate><category>Backing Types &amp; Coatings</category><category>grit-60</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-240</category><description>Learn when to choose cloth or fiber abrasive backings and how open coat sandpaper improves cut, reduces loading, and optimizes sanding workflows.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="cloth-vs-fiber-backings-with-open-coat-sandpaper"&gt;Cloth vs Fiber Backings with Open Coat Sandpaper&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It starts on a Saturday morning with a surface that matters. Maybe it’s a maple tabletop you milled last fall, or a set of welded brackets you promised to deliver before lunch. You switch on the dust extractor, index a fresh disc, and take the first pass. Within seconds, you know if the setup is right: the abrasive either cuts cleanly or smears; it either stays cool and sheds swarf or loads, glazing the face and burning the work. This isn’t luck. It’s backing selection, grain geometry, and coating density working together. For a lot of workflows—especially on resinous woods, body filler, aluminum, and painted surfaces—open coat sandpaper keeps the cut alive by leaving voids between abrasive grains that evacuate debris instead of embedding it. But even the right coat pattern underperforms if the backing can’t transmit force, resist heat, or conform to the surface you’re shaping.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/28.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/01/07/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/when-to-choose-cloth-or-fiber-backings-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Anti Clog Design For Painted Surfaces</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 13:33:05 +0000</pubDate><category>Backing Types &amp; Coatings</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-100</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>wet sanding</category><category>dry sanding</category><category>sanding block</category><description>Learn how open coat sandpaper and anti-clog coatings deliver smoother results on painted surfaces, with pro tips, gear choices, and troubleshooting.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="open-coat-sandpaper-for-painted-surfaces"&gt;Open Coat Sandpaper for Painted Surfaces&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The weekend starts with a small promise to yourself: fresh paint, clean lines, a room that feels lighter when you walk in. But before the color goes up, something else has to come down—old paint, a rough patch, a drippy corner where the brush ran heavy last time. You pull out a sheet of sandpaper and, for a few strokes, it feels right. Then the dust rolls into pills, the sheet clogs, the finish scratches, and you’re wondering why this simple prep step feels like a fight. If you’ve ever paused mid-sand to pick off gummy paint from your paper, you’ve already met the enemy. The fix doesn’t start with elbow grease; it starts with choosing the right abrasive. On painted surfaces, open coat sandpaper—often paired with an anti-clog “no-fill” layer—doesn’t just last longer; it changes the way the surface behaves while you work.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/12.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/20/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/anti-clog-design-for-painted-surfaces-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Stearated Coatings For Load Resistance</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 04 Dec 2025 14:21:48 +0000</pubDate><category>Backing Types &amp; Coatings</category><category>grit-100</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-220</category><category>dry sanding</category><description>Beat clogging and heat. Learn how stearated coatings and open coat sandpaper work together for faster, cleaner sanding with pro workflows and tips.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="open-coat-sandpaper--stearated-coatings-guide"&gt;Open Coat Sandpaper &amp;amp; Stearated Coatings Guide&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s Saturday morning in the shop—the kind where the coffee cools on the bench because you’re in a flow state. You square up your random-orbit sander over a pine cabinet door you’ve been meaning to refinish. Two passes in, the pad stalls, dust smears into a chalky cake, and the disc stops cutting. We’ve all been there: soft wood, resin pockets, a touch of old varnish, and sandpaper that loads up faster than you can tap it clean. That’s when I reach for open coat sandpaper paired with a stearated coating. It’s the combination that keeps abrasive cutting edges exposed while a dry “lubricant” layer sheds paint, pitch, and finish dust instead of letting it fuse to the grit.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/25.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/04/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/stearated-coatings-for-load-resistance-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Paper Weight And Flexibility Differences</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 20 Nov 2025 05:56:56 +0000</pubDate><category>Backing Types &amp; Coatings</category><category>grit-150</category><category>orbital sander</category><category>sanding block</category><category>grit progression</category><category>wet sanding</category><description>Understand paper weight, flexibility, and when to use open coat sandpaper for cleaner cuts, fewer clogs, and pro-grade finishes in wood and metalwork.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="open-coat-sandpaper-paper-weight-and-flexibility"&gt;Open Coat Sandpaper, Paper Weight, and Flexibility&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Saturday morning, mug of coffee steaming on the bench. The shop is still cool, and the only sound is your block plane sliding across a maple board. You’re smoothing a reclaimed slab into a dining table that has to look heirloom, not “weekend project.” You switch to abrasive work—this is where most projects are won or lost. Pull a sheet from the drawer and you can tell instantly: too stiff and it will flatten the gentle chamfer you’ve planed; too flimsy and it will telegraph every ridge from your fingertips. You also know the species: maple burns if you let a clogged sheet skate across it. That’s where choice matters—paper weight, flexibility, and whether open coat sandpaper will let the dust clear instead of loading the sheet like wet snow on a shovel.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/11.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/20/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/paper-weight-and-flexibility-differences-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Film Backing For Uniform Fine Scratches</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/08/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/08/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper/</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Nov 2025 13:28:53 +0000</pubDate><category>Backing Types &amp; Coatings</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-400</category><category>grit-600</category><category>grit-800</category><category>orbital sander</category><category>dry sanding</category><description>Engineer-tested guidance on film-backed, open coat sandpaper for uniform fine scratches, with data, setups, and grit sequencing tips.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="open-coat-sandpaper-on-film-for-fine-scratches"&gt;Open coat sandpaper on film for fine scratches&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The raking light told the truth I didn’t want to hear. After an hour shaping a walnut desktop, the surface looked perfect under diffuse shop lights—but the morning sun found every swirl and pigtail. I’d sanded carefully, stepped through grits, and kept the pad moving. Still, the micro-scratches telegraphed through as soon as I wiped on mineral spirits. That’s the moment I switched to film-backed abrasives and, crucially, open coat sandpaper for the early and mid-grits. The difference wasn’t subtle; it was measurable.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/08/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/08/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/08/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/facebook/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/08/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/08/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/08/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/instagram/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/08/film-backing-for-uniform-fine-scratches-open-coat-sandpaper/cards/pinterest/film-backing-for-uniform-fin